description: Coefficients of Jacobi Eisenstein series of index 1 and weight 8.
references: M. Eichler and D. Zagier, The Theory of Jacobi Forms, Birkhauser, 1985, p. 141.
formula: The series is t3^3*[t3^12-15*(t3^8*t2^4)/8+15*(t3^4*t2^8)/16-7*(t2^12)/128] where tj=theta_j(z) is the associated weight 15/2 form.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
extensions: More terms from Kok Seng Chua (chuaks(AT)ihpc.nus.edu.sg), May 26 2000
a(31) corrected by _Sean A. Irvine_, Jan 20 2016
